  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a developer and marketer, I want to integrate Play Store metadata into my workflow so that the Play Store is always up to date.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nDuring the beta launch, we realized that we neglected the Play Store metadata. Images were old, and the copy still referred to alpha. Since Play Store management is silo'd with a handful of users, and the responsibility is split between #mobile-team and #marketing it has been hard to stay on top of this.\r\n\r\nStatus also intends to localize the app description and images but it is incredibly tedious to manage this in the Play admin. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\nWe use Fastlane to manage Play Store releases and Fastlane has a nifty feature to manage metadata that gives metadata visibility in this repo and allows anyone to see and edit screenshots, descriptions, etc. It can even manage several languages!!! We just need to activate this feature.\r\n\r\n",
